library(tidyverse)
# Add any other libraries here
library(readxl)
library(janitor)
# load your data 
 
BirdLife <- read_csv("/Users/reyr/R/Final_project/Birds/ELEData/TraitData/AVONET1_BirdLife.csv")
## Rows: 11009 Columns: 37
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (13): Species1, Family1, Order1, Avibase.ID1, Mass.Source, Mass.Refs.Oth...
## dbl (24): Sequence, Total.individuals, Female, Male, Unknown, Complete.measu...
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
Birdlife_Long <- BirdLife %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(Female, Male),
    names_to = "gender",
    values_to = "individuals"
  )


Birdlife_Long %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = (Wing.Length), 
                 y = (Mass), 
                 colour = Habitat, 
                 size = individuals, 
                 alpha = 0.3,
                  )) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm") +
  guides(size = FALSE, alpha = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(. ~ Habitat, scales = "free") +
  coord_cartesian(
    xlim = c(0, 400),
    ylim = c(0, 3000)
  )
